                <h1>How to Reduce Background Noise with Your Microphone</h1>
                <p>Microphones often pick up background noise, which can detract from audio quality in recordings or live broadcasts. To minimize this issue, consider using directional microphones, adjusting mic placement, or employing noise-canceling technology. Additionally, controlling the recording environment can significantly enhance sound clarity.</p>
